sec.p:
Spacing of banana plants varies with the type of bananas to be planted. “Bogoya” a local variety of banana is widely spaced whereas short ones such as “Nakytengu” banana variety which was considered for this study is closely spaced. For Nakytengu variety, a spacing of 3 m × 3 m in between the holes gives a banana plant population of 450 per acre and 750 to 900 banana plants per hectare, with a daily water requirement of 25 L d−1 [20]. This was the water per meter length of row required, and therefore, the total water required per day for 1 acre of Nakytengu banana plantation was obtained from Eq. 1 [18].
1TH2O=TLRm×RH2OLm−1d−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
