				\begin{document}$$ {T}_{H_2O}={T}_{LR}\ (m)\times {R}_{H_2O}\left(L\ {m}^{-1}{d}^{-1}\right)\kern1em $$\end{document}

where TH20 is total water required per day, TLR the total length of rows and RH2O is water requirement (L m−1 d−1). Given that 1 acre is 4046.7 m2 and considering this area as square that is to say 63.6 m by 63.6 m, then the total length of rows was obtained through dividing the total area of banana plantation by length of rows [18].
