The flow rate of submain can be determined by using the total discharge and the required number of sections to be irrigated as given by Eq. 6. When the field is in trapezoidal, triangular and not rectangular in shape, the design can be made by adjusting the total discharge so the design chart made for rectangular fields can be used directly. Since the submain length is normally short, the submain size is designed for a single size and submain slope is assumed to be uniform and downslope [22].
