where V = speed to the height h, Vo is speed to the height ho (frequently referred to as 10 m height) and ∝ is the friction coefficient or Hellman exponent. “This coefficient is frequently assumed as a value of 1/7 for open land and is a function of the topography at a specific site,” [27]. Table 9 is the friction coefficient of various landscapes.
