“The capacity factor is defined as the actual power output over a certain period of time as a proportion of a wind turbine/facility’s maximum capacity” [30]. Equation 26 was then used to estimate the actual rated power and a capacity factor CP of 0.30 was selected for the study (that is to say, 30% of time wind machine produces energy at the rated power).
26Power ratingCapacity factor=0.2920.30=0.97kW≈1kW\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
